  "text": "Sodium potassium adenosine triphosphatase (Na/K ATPase) has been reported to be responsible for the energy dependent extrusion of sodium ions (Na + ) and uptake of potassium ions (K + ), an important part of the maintenance of ionic homeostasis [CITATION_1] . Damage to membrane lipids with impaired Na/K ATPase functioning subsequent to arsenic induced oxidative stress could be important in altering Anat Cell Biol 2012;45:229-240 237",
